# PSAP Cybersecurity Research

Academic research applying established security frameworks and 
original investigation methods to cyber resilience in Public Safety 
Answering Point (PSAP) environments.

## Papers

### [`security-operations-psap-resilience.pdf`](./security-operations-psap-resilience.pdf)
**Security Operations in Public Safety: Applying the CISSP Incident 
Lifecycle to PSAP Cyber Resilience**

Applies the CISSP Domain 7 (Security Operations) incident management 
lifecycle to the PSAP environment, using the 2016 Arizona telephony 
denial of service (TDoS) incident as a case study. Covers preparation 
and prevention, detection and analysis, response and containment, and 
recovery and post-incident improvement, with practical recommendations 
for PSAP technical leaders.

### [`tdos-mitigation-investigation.pdf`](./tdos-mitigation-investigation.pdf)
**Investigation into Mitigating Telephony Denial of Service Threats to 
PSAPs Through Layered Security Practices**

A management investigation report combining a literature review, a 
structured interview with a PSAP director, and an original public 
survey to assess how layered TDoS mitigation strategies (call 
filtering, geo-fencing, policy-based routing) are understood and 
implemented in practice versus industry standards (NENA).
